3557	  \textit{Project-bespoke gap-fill (instance).}
3558	  The forgetful functor from sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules to the underlying sheaves of
3559	  abelian groups preserves epimorphisms: if \(g : S_2 \to S_3\) is an epimorphism of
3560	  \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules then the induced morphism of underlying abelian sheaves is an
3561	  epimorphism. This is the one small instance unlocking the passage from a module epimorphism to
3562	  local surjectivity in Lemma~\ref{lem:affine_surj_of_vanishing}.
3563	\end{lemma}
3564	\begin{proof}
3565	  \uses{lem:toSheaf_preservesFiniteColimits, lem:preservesEpi_of_preservesColimitsOfShape_mathlib}
3566	  The functor \(\mathrm{toSheaf}\,R\) preserves finite colimits
3567	  (Lemma~\ref{lem:toSheaf_preservesFiniteColimits}); in particular it preserves colimits of shape
3568	  \(\mathrm{WalkingSpan}\), which is a finite shape. A functor that preserves pushouts preserves
3569	  epimorphisms (Lemma~\ref{lem:preservesEpi_of_preservesColimitsOfShape_mathlib}), so
3570	  \(\mathrm{toSheaf}\,R\) carries the epimorphism \(g\) to an epimorphism of abelian sheaves.
3571	\end{proof}
